[A recent study mapping lymphatic filariasis (LF) in Zambia concluded that "LF was found to be surprisingly widespread in Zambia, although in most places with low prevalence" (Mwase ET, et al. Mapping the geographical distribution of lymphatic filariasis in Zambia. PLoS Negl Trop Dis. 2014 Feb 20;8(2):e2714). The blood samples were analysed by the Binax rapid antigen detection assay, detecting a _Wuchereria bancrofti_ antigen, and whether this test is cross reactive to _Mansonella perstans_ is not known. - Mod.EP

